<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>HENDRICKSON SUSPENSION SYSTEMS - BUSHING REPLACEMENT - BEAM END WITH BAR PIN DESIGN</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="replace" graphiccount="2">
        <title>BEAM END WITH BAR PIN DESIGN</title>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Remove (On Vehicle) One End Only</title>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>As of October 1992, International vehicles built with Hendrickson (walking beam) suspension
                        series U/UE, RT/RTE, RS will have the BAR PIN DESIGN on the beam end (
                        <hotlnk xrefid="f0300616">Figure 16</hotlnk>).
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <figure id="f0300616" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g0300616" filename="../figg03/G0300616.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 16. Bar Pin Design</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1.MOUNTING BRACKET (WELDED ONTO AXLE)</callout1>
                    <callout1>2.BAR PIN</callout1>
                    <callout1>3.BOLT/WASHER</callout1>
                    <callout1>4.BEAM END</callout1>
                    <callout1>5.NUT/WASHER</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>The vehicles built at the assembly plant will not have BAR PIN alignment capabilities. The
                        service kits will have alignment shims provided with the kit (
                        <hotlnk xrefid="f0300617">Figure 17</hotlnk>). This alignment procedure will be covered in GROUP
                        03- SUSPENSION ALIGNMENT section in the CTS-5000 Master Service Manual.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <figure id="f0300617" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g0300617" filename="../figg03/G0300617.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 17. Alignment Shims</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1.MOUNTING BRACKET</callout1>
                    <callout1>2.BAR PIN WITH SHIMS</callout1>
                    <callout1>3.BOLT/WASHER</callout1>
                    <callout1>4.BEAM END</callout1>
                    <callout1>5.NUT/WASHER</callout1>
                    <callout1>6.ADJUSTER SHIMS</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Block front wheels.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Raise axles and support vehicle by the frame. Use frame stands.</para>
                <specpara>
                    <warning>
                        <para>A jack must never be used alone to support vehicle while under-chassis service is being
                            per- formed. The jack may lower and serious personal injury could result. Always support
                            vehicle with floor stands.
                        </para>
                    </warning>
                </specpara>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove wheels from the axle on the side that is being serviced (front or rear depending
                    on the beam end being serviced). Refer to Group 17-RIMS, WHEELS and TIRES in the CTS-5000 Master
                    Service Manual.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove beam saddle nuts, washers and caps on the side being serviced. Support beam with
                    jack.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove nuts, washers and bolts securing bar pin to bracket.</para>
                <specpara>
                    <note>
                        <para>If bolts are difficult to remove, use an air hammer to loosen bolts.</para>
                    </note>
                </specpara>
                <specpara>
                    <note>
                        <para>The upper torque rods may have to be disconnected at the top of the axle, and the axle
                            rotated to a more vertical position to assist in the removal of the bar pin.
                        </para>
                    </note>
                </specpara>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Lower beam to give access to beam end.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Using SPECIAL TOOL per tool instructions, remove bar pin. Refer to SPECIAL TOOLS,
                    <hotlnk document="s03006s_30.xml" xrefid="f0300644">Figure 44</hotlnk>,
                    <hotlnk document="s03006s_30.xml" xrefid="f0300645">Figure 45</hotlnk>, and
                    <hotlnk document="s03006s_30.xml" xrefid="f0300646">Figure 46</hotlnk>.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Using emery cloth, clean beam end of any nicks or burrs. Also clean new bar pin to
                    remove manufacturer coating.
                </para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Install</title>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>Before installation of new bar pin, lubricate beam end and bushing O.D. with chassis grease.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>Do not use old bar pin nuts or bolts.</para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install bar pin using SPECIAL TOOLS instructions in
                    <hotlnk document="s03006s_30.xml" xrefid="f0300644">Figure 44</hotlnk>
                    ,
                    <hotlnk document="s03006s_30.xml" xrefid="f0300645">Figure 45</hotlnk>
                    , and
                    <hotlnk document="s03006s_30.xml" xrefid="f0300646">Figure 46</hotlnk>
                    .
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Using jack raise beam into position.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install new bolts, washers and nuts. Tighten to specifications; refer to the
                    <hotlnk document="s03006s_29.xml" xrefid="hl0300604">TORQUE CHART</hotlnk>.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install saddle caps. Tighten cap nuts to specifications. Refer to the
                    <hotlnk document="s03006s_29.xml" xrefid="hl0300604">TORQUE CHART</hotlnk>.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove jack from beam.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install wheels. Refer to GROUP 17- RIMS, WHEELS AND TIRES in the CTS-5000 Master Service
                    Manual.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove frame stands and put vehicle back into service.</para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
